    <item>
      <title>Sad Behavior</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Karana&amp;message.id=100#M100</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;This is both to vent my frustrations in general and to give people a heads up of all the bad attitudes I come across on our server.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Every server has it's hot zones.&amp;nbsp; You know, the ones where people go to get good xp fast.&amp;nbsp; On our server, Paludal Caverns is that zone.&amp;nbsp; I am no longer surprised that every time I go there with a low level alt, that I have problems with KSers.&amp;nbsp; It seems like every time I go there to PL myself someone always wants to force me out of my camp or KS me.&amp;nbsp; Now I know that technically there is no such thing as a camp.&amp;nbsp; But anyone that is courteous will be respectful and leave someone alone when they are trying to hunt solo.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Take camp 1 in PC for example.&amp;nbsp; Two hills, four tents, plenty of mobs for two seperate groups to hunt.&amp;nbsp; One group each side right?&amp;nbsp; Well, it seems that some people think it is wrong for a person to want to take two tents to solo, but it is ok for them to attempt to KS that soloer until they get fed up and leave so that all four tents are left for one group.&amp;nbsp; If you ask me, that is just plain wrong.&amp;nbsp; I've seen groups split that camp nicely many times, but there is always one person that thrives on ruining someone else's day that HAS to be a pest.&amp;nbsp; Easy solution for the soloer would be to move on and ignore the bad apples.&amp;nbsp; But is it fair to that person that they should be walked all over while the rude person(s) get their way?&amp;nbsp; Using /report, /petition and /ignore, or talking to their guild leaders doesn't always help much.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I don't know if this post will get deleted or not but I am fed up, and I am sure I am not alone.&amp;nbsp; I am going to use this thread to post names of KSers I have come accross in Norrath.&amp;nbsp; I don't mean the ones that do it once by accident.&amp;nbsp; I mean the ones that persist in pestering you until you are forced to give up and log off in frustration before you do something stupid to stoop to their level.&amp;nbsp; I will not list the names of the guilds they belonged to at the time because people change guilds, and it isnt' the guild's fault that an individual chooses to make them look bad with their disrespectful behavior.&amp;nbsp; Some of you will read this and think I am just as dumb as the newbs acting so rudely.&amp;nbsp; Sad thing is that a lot of the people behavign this way are people that have been playing a while already, some of them grown adults.&amp;nbsp; Why does being a pixelated character suddenly make it ok to be an ass?&amp;nbsp; If this post survives and doesn't get deleted, I will add names as I come across the less savory people I meet in Norrath.&amp;nbsp; If you want to add to this thread please, do not include guild names.&amp;nbsp; Do not post false information.&amp;nbsp; Be honest and don't use this as an excuse to defame an otherwise good person.&amp;nbsp; This is my way of venting, and putting out the names of people that don't want to be your friend, don't want to play nice, they just want to ruin your day.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Odesi - At the time of my issue with him he was a lvl 18 DE necromancer without a guild.&amp;nbsp; (surprise surprise)&amp;nbsp; I was happily PLing my level 14 warrior in PC at camp 1.&amp;nbsp; Had several group offers but I chose to solo instead.&amp;nbsp; I love to PL my friends and guildies and nice people i meet in zones.&amp;nbsp; But when it comes to groups of strangers it is hard for me because I always feel bad if I can't keep up and someone dies.&amp;nbsp; So I politely decline each offer for a group, stating I am simply there to get some fast xp so I can leave PC.&amp;nbsp; After all, I always end up having trouble there, but hey, the xp is great!&amp;nbsp; 20 minutes go by and I am easily holding my own with just two tents.&amp;nbsp; I am not being greedy, I dont' need all four tents.&amp;nbsp; After all, a group could come in and need a camp to pull from.&amp;nbsp; Fair is fair.&amp;nbsp; Suddenly this Odesi person comes in with a group of friends.&amp;nbsp; Offers me a group, I politely decline.&amp;nbsp; He proceeds to tell me "well we are camping here so we will just over power you."&amp;nbsp; I tell him that I have been there for 20 minutes and that there are two perfectly good tents on the other hill of the camp open, just take those.&amp;nbsp; He does not seem to want those two and has his group attack everything I pull in an attempt to KS me.&amp;nbsp; They only succeed in stealing my xp a few times but I am beyond annoyed at this point.&amp;nbsp; How is it fair for this person to come in and tell me they are taking MY camp?&amp;nbsp; After OOCing a couple times for them to please leave me be they continue their rude behavior.&amp;nbsp; I move to the other side of the camp, the two tents they were ignoring, and pull from there, only to have them KS me some more.&amp;nbsp; They think it's dumb for me to want to solo two tents, yet they think it is fair for them to have all four.&amp;nbsp; This sucks big time.&amp;nbsp; I do a petition.&amp;nbsp; I send a report.&amp;nbsp; No GMs on at the time so by the time anything gets done about it, they will be logged off.&amp;nbsp; Odesi keeps running from my alt to my main, kissing them on the cheek, and telling me in /ooc to "try to compete sweetie".&amp;nbsp; By this time I am wishing I could send an incurable virus to this person's computer just to show then that playing EQ is a privilege not a right.&amp;nbsp; I tell him in /ooc that I am not his sweetie and that with his attitude he won't have many friends other than his fellow KSing Natzis.&amp;nbsp; By this time enough has been said back and forth in /ooc that the rest of the zone is getting sick of it, even though everyone that has said anything has agreed with me whole heartedly.&amp;nbsp; It seems they too have had KSing issues today....sigh....&amp;nbsp; But what can I do about it?&amp;nbsp; Nothing.&amp;nbsp; Abso-friggin-lutely nothing.&amp;nbsp; I can only hope that one day, he gets what he deserves.&amp;nbsp; The truly sad thing about this is that one of my guildies reported to me that the previous night, they too had issues with Odesi, only it was another one of his alts.&amp;nbsp; Even worse, this other alt is in one of our ally guilds!&amp;nbsp; It is so sad that someone would be so cowardly as to hide behind an alt to make trouble and be so two faced as to act as if they are your friend on another character.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Twotime - A barbarian something or other at the time of the incident.&amp;nbsp; This person was guilded at the time.&amp;nbsp; He was also grouped with Odesi, the jerk off from above.&amp;nbsp; He never said a word, as if letting Odesi do all the talking made his actions acceptable.&amp;nbsp; He just continued to attack everything I pulled regardless of the fact that the first 10 times I asked them to leave me alone, it was nicely.&amp;nbsp; I sent a tell to a high lvl person in his guild.&amp;nbsp; Just wanted to inform them that they had a KSer in their guild that was making them look bad.&amp;nbsp; You know a guild has potential when its members actually try to do something about a bad apple instead of just letting it slide.&amp;nbsp; However, when only one person makes an effort, it makes you think poorly about that guild, which is wrong because not everyone in a guild neccessarily has a bad attitude.&amp;nbsp; The high lvl person I sent a tell to tried to get an officer's attention with no luck.&amp;nbsp; He even came to the zone to speak with Twotime but received no response from him.&amp;nbsp; Makes me so angry that someone would care so little about the image they are projecting on the guild they belong to.&amp;nbsp; Whether they care or not, there ARE people that strive to make a guild succeed.&amp;nbsp; People like Twotime just don't care because they think that if they get kicked out, big deal, they can always join another guild.&amp;nbsp; But eventually, word will spread about what an Arse womeone is and no guild wants them.&amp;nbsp; They go from Asset status to liability status.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
