    <item>
      <title>Good Idea: Please help spread the word</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Karana&amp;message.id=65#M65</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;Hello, my name is Arkticwynd Wyntyrfury' Wolfmoon.&amp;nbsp; I am the guild leader of the Arctic Wolves on the Karana Server.&amp;nbsp; I have a suggestion for adding a guild management&amp;nbsp;feature that would make the life of a guild leader and guild officer much easier.&amp;nbsp; If you are a guild leader/officer, or if you just plain like my idea, please use the /feedback option in the game, or send an email to: EQFeedback@soe.sony.com&amp;nbsp; and submit feedback similar to what I am listing below.&amp;nbsp; This is a copy of the email I sent to SoE:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;I feel that a "Banned Characters" option should be added to the guild management window for all servers.&amp;nbsp; It should work the way the "friends" and "ignore" lists do.&amp;nbsp; The guild leader and officers should be able to type in the names of people that are banned from the guild.&amp;nbsp; Then members should be able to view those names by clicking on the tab or button that says "Banned Characters".&amp;nbsp; I also think that this feature should allow the /guildinvite command to recognize other characters on the banned person's account.&amp;nbsp; I am not saying it should tell you all the names of the banned person's alts.&amp;nbsp; Instead, if a banned person tries to get an alt invited into the guild, when the /guildinvite command is issued, a text box should pop up saying "This person cannot join your guild.&amp;nbsp; They have been banned on another character."&amp;nbsp; This would enable guild leaders to keep vengeful, bitter, bad apples out of their guilds.&amp;nbsp; I have seen several good guilds either have on-going problems or go down in flames becasue of one or more people that continued to causes trouble for them.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;I know I would benefit a great deal from this.&amp;nbsp; For example:&amp;nbsp; There is a woman on my server that I do not get along with in RL.&amp;nbsp; She was kicked out of the last guild she and I both happened to be in, becasue she continually broke guild rules by harassing people.&amp;nbsp; She takes great pleasure in harassing me in the game, something I am workign on resolving at this very moment.&amp;nbsp; I know the names of four of her toons.&amp;nbsp; She has tried to get one of them in my guild since&amp;nbsp;it was&amp;nbsp;created.&amp;nbsp; However, she still has four character slots she could have toons in that I do not know about.&amp;nbsp; I don't necessarily want to know who all her toons are, but it would help keep her out of my guild if my idea was implemented.&amp;nbsp; I have talked to quite a few people on my server about this, both guild leaders and non-guild leaders.&amp;nbsp; They have all loved my idea.&amp;nbsp; What should I do to get Sony to seriously consider this idea?&amp;nbsp; Do I need to go around asking people to send feedback until they type their fingers to the bone?&amp;nbsp; I honestly feel this would benefit a great number of guilds.&amp;nbsp; I have already used the in-game /feedback option.&amp;nbsp; I know you are very busy so the likely hood of a response is slim to none.&amp;nbsp; But that was over two months ago, and I have not heard anything on it.&amp;nbsp; It would be nice to at least know if this suggestion is being remotely considered.&amp;nbsp; Thank you for your time.&amp;nbsp; Have a nice day.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;Sincerely,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;Arkticwynd Wyntyrfury' Wolfmoon&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;I do not know how many guild leaders out there experience problems with persistent people that have been kicked out of their guild for one reason or another.&amp;nbsp; But anything that makes the life of a guild leader easier, is a good idea to me!&amp;nbsp; If you support my idea, please use the /feedback option or send SoE an email similar to the one I pasted above.&amp;nbsp; Feel free to offer up suggestions that would perfect this idea as well.&amp;nbsp; One person can come up with a good idea, but many people coming together to perfect it turns it into a great idea.&amp;nbsp; Your comments would be appreciated.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana color=#cc0000 size=2&gt;May each respective Deity bless you, and my the Wolves guide your paths to great adventure!&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
